Text.Value: You'd have sent me, and I'd have died a particularly stupid hero.
I've seen enough murder, thanks. I'm not interested.
Including someone matching our killer's description. Which is odd, as it's been out of business as long as I've lived here.
|RANDOM FLAMING FIST LEADING A NO-DEVELLA NO-VALERIA FLOW (SHORTER)|

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The player takes a second to catch their breath. They've just defeated a serial killer they've been on the trail of for hours. They survey the scene, and then their attention is drawn off-stage.

Text.Value: I think the Investigator meant to say 'please'. We need your help to stop the cult.
It's all right for you, you've got bloody wings! Fists, ready weapons, prepare for - oh.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Devella retorts to the hollyphant, before barking orders at the flaming fists, ready for combat, before she spots the player.

Text.Value: Not working alone? What on earth do you -
Y- yes, very good Devella. We suspect that's where the Bhaalist cult is situated. Whatever sick ritual they're up to must be stopped.
|DEVELLA LEADING A NO-VALERIA FLOW|
I agree. Baldur's Gate lends you its gratitude today. Good luck, friend.
Solid work putting this one down. Can't have been easy. So, did you figure out why he was killing?
FISTS! TO ME! DEFEND OUR CITY!
Devella. Compose yourself. Look, if you change your mind, go to Candulhallows. I implore you. If not... stay safe, citizen.
I'm in.
This is fantastic news. I don't know what we'd have done if you said no.
Before you see this through, mortal - thank you. This city needs more folk like you.
Say, I don't appreciate your tone. I am the Grand Investigator of the Fla-
He was insane, kept talking about bringing people's hands to his god.
That's rather excellent news. Although it might not be as simple as stopping one killer.
You managed to stop this maniac - we couldn't even find him. Stands to reason that you're our best bet at stopping the Bhaalists.
Why can't you do it?
A few of them read it off a note they had - perhaps the killer you've just put down has one on his person.
That's so gracious of you, Investigator. Sorry about that, they came straight from Sharess' Caress.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The last sentence is said as an aside to the player, with devella miming drinking with her hand

Text.Value: You're quite right. It seems the Lord of Murder has been busy in Baldur's Gate.
I did some digging, turns out Candulhallow's Tombstones boasts quite the sinister foot traffic these days.
We tried to get into Candulhallow's. The cultists we saw spoke some sort of pass phrase, but we haven't found what it is yet.
Well, thank Helm it didn't come to that. And, more pressingly, thank you.
The cult are a charming lot, I want only the best for them.
This sounds dangerous - I'm out.
Oh indeed. It's you. Again. I must say - you've a real knack for sorting these things out.
I'd wager the whole damn city's lucky you got here. Now, I shall inspect the -
Ascension. It was part of a ritual for Bhaal.
Any idea what to expect when I get there?
It's not sorted out, the killer wasn't working alone.
That's some bollocks. Without you, people will die.
Oh dear gods. All that viscera... I'm feeling a bit q - queasy. Constable Fountainread, take point on this one. It'll be good experience.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: the q - queasy here indicates valeria Valeria floats back at the end of this, retching

Text.Value: What do you... Oh. Oh. You're one of them. How did I not -
This fellow had something a little bit more involved than a hobby.
[EVIL PATH] But if I did that, I couldn't become an avatar of slaughter. That sounds no fun at all.
|VALERIA LEADING A NO-DEVELLA FLOW|
And you've got a real knack for missing all the action.
Everyone needs a hobby, I guess.
So, it seems there's only one thing left to do. Once you destroy this Bhaalist cult, this whole business can be put to rest.
Move your tiny legs faster, Devella, or they'll get away!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: We see Valeria, Devella, and a small cohort of Flaming fists running towards the player.

Text.Value: Unfortunately, he wasn't the only one - there's a Bhaalist cult at work here.
I'm just lucky I got here in time.
I'm in.

Synopsis: Dialog after kill Dolor in Figaro's Cosmetic Shop. Valeria alive.
